text:
Washington Square East, east side, from Washington Place, to Waverly Place (left), showing the University of the City of New York, erected 1832-35.

Prior to 1890's

Gift of Urbrock Collection
title: Manhattan: Washington Square East - Washington Place

text:
New York University, Washington Square East, from Washington to Waverly Places, showing 1-2 Washington Square North. This is the new building, erected about 1900 on the site of the old New York University building, and at first occupied by the American Book Company.

July, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Washington Square East - Washington Place
